      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the pastry by rubbing the cold butter into the flour, sugar, and salt until the mixture resembles breadcrumbs. Add the egg yolk and cold water and bring together into a dough. Wrap and chill for 30 minutes. Roll out and line a 23 cm tart tin, pressing into the sides. Return to the refrigerator while you prepare the filling.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Toss the apple slices with the sugar, cinnamon, and lemon juice. Leave for 10 minutes, then pour off any pooled juice. Make the crumble by rubbing the cold butter into the flour, oats, and dark brown sugar until it clumps in pea-sized pieces.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 190°C conventional (170°C fan). Fill the chilled pastry case with the apple slices, pressing down gently. Scatter the crumble evenly over the top. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes until the crumble is golden and the pastry is cooked at the sides. Cool for at least 20 minutes before slicing; the filling sets as it cools.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
